<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d7efdff3-06d5-4d37-a97e-5e7b937fcc2c_1637560263.5852876.png" width = 650 />
</td>
<td><code>T</code> found in the BST.</br> It has no children which means it is a leaf node.</br> So, we can delete it just by updating <code>T</code>'s parent pointer to null and then deleting <code>T</code></br></br>In example, we simply updated right pointer of <code>5</code>'s parent node-<code>4</code> as null</td>
</tr>
<tr></tr>
<tr>

