</td>
<td><code>T</code> found in BST and only has the right child/subtree</br>Cant directly delete <code>T</code> as it has its right child that must remain in the BST</br>we <b>update child pointer of parent of <code>T</code> to the right child of <code>T</code></b></br></br>In example, we updated left child pointer of <code>12</code> to point at <code>11</code> which is right child of the node to be deleted-<code>10</code></td>
</tr>
<tr></tr>
