When find the node to delete, always find the least number which is greater than the value to delete, which is in the right sub tree of the current node. if one of the sub tree of this current node is null, then directly return the other sub tree. Use findMin(node) to find the value to be replaced, then delete the leaf node.
```
class Solution {
    public TreeNode deleteNode(TreeNode root, int key) {
        if(root == null) return root;
        if(key < root.val) root.left = deleteNode(root.left, key);
        else if(key > root.val) root.right = deleteNode(root.right, key);
        else {
            if(root.left == null) return root.right;
            else if(root.right == null) return root.left;
            else {
                int val = findMin(root.right);
                root.val = val;
                root.right = deleteNode(root.right, val);
            }
        }
        return root;
    }

    private int findMin(TreeNode root) {
        while(root.left != null) root = root.left;
        return root.val;
    }
}
```

