## IDEA :
* First search for the node which is having value as target value.
* Now we have to delete that Node. It means if we are not having left subtree then directly return the right subtree as well as vice-versa.
* But if we are having both subtree then we have to find the smallest Node in the right subtree which will be left most Node.

* Now replace the value of root Node with the lowest right subtree and Delete that Node.

**Implementation :**
