The idea is to count each character's frequency in a fmap. Then create a frequency list to keep track of characters that occur for that each frequency. For example if 'a' occurs 5 times in the string, then the list at freq[5] would contain character 'a' in it. 
Then just iterate the freqlist array from the end and store our answer accordingly. 
Time complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)
Where n is the length of the string.
