# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Take a map and count the frequency of each character.
and taken a vector pair of type int and char
#### vector<pair<int,char>>v;

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
I have taken a iterator to iterate through map 
and pushed this value and keys into a vector. 
and pushed values(it.second) and keys(it.first)
```
for(auto it: mp){
         v.push_back({it.second,it.first});
       }
```
This vector is sorted in descending order i.e 5,4,3,2,1
#### sort(v.begin(),v.end(),greater<pair<int,char>>());

NOW iterate through the vector and I have used string constructor 
it will append string(it.first,it.second)  i.e(5,e)  (FIVE TIMES E )
into the res string
```
for(auto it: v){
         res=res+string(it.first,it.second);
       }
```
FINALLY WE WILL RETURN THE RESULT i.e res


