***Explanation:***
1. Iterate through the string and store the count of each character in an unordered_map
2. Now we have each character and its count in the unordered_map
3. Insert the count of each character and the character itself into the multimap i.e {count, character} (Here we use multimap because there can be 2 characters that can have same number of occurences Eg: aabb)
4. Since we used greater<int> in our multimap the count will be stored in the descending order.
5. Now we have occurence of each charater in descending order and just need to iterate the multimap and update the string.

