**Follow-up: what if the characters are sorted alphabetically if the characters have the same frequency ?**

**1.  wrapper class & overwrite lt, eq comparables**
* Time: O(NlogN)
* Space: O(N)
```
class Solution:
    def frequencySort(self, s: str) -> str:
        class Element:
            def __init__(self, freq, ch):
                self.freq = freq
                self.ch = ch    
            def __lt__(self, other):
                return self.freq < other.freq or (self.freq == other.freq and self.ch > other.ch)
            def __eq__(self, other):
                return self.freq == other.freq and self.ch == other.ch
        k = len(set(s))
        pq = [Element(float('-inf'), '') for _ in range(k)]
        for ch, freq in collections.Counter(s).items():
            heapq.heappushpop(pq, Element(freq, ch))   
        res = ''
        while pq:
            elem = heapq.heappop(pq)
            res += elem.freq * elem.ch
        return res[::-1]
```

