# Approach

* Storing all characters with its frequency in an unordered_map
* Then Storing back the characters with its frequency in a priority queue<<int,char>> to later access it in sorted order of their decreasing frequency.
* Then just add character by character to a new string by accessing top of priority_queue as the character with most frequency will be at top 




# Complexity
- Time complexity:  O(n * log(n))
If you have an empty priority queue to which you want to add n items, one at a time, then the complexity is O(n * log(n)).



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string frequencySort(string s) {
        string s1="";

        priority_queue<pair<int,char>> q;
        unordered_map<char,int> m;
        for(auto ch:s) m[ch]++;

        for(auto a:m){
            q.push({a.second,a.first});
        }
        m.clear();
        while(!q.empty()){
            auto p=q.top();
            while(p.first--) s1+=p.second;
            q.pop();
        }
        return s1;
    }
};


```

