# Intuition
Using Priority Queue for Efficient time complexity. 

Priority Queue: is an abstract data type that is similar to a queue, and every element has some priority value associated with it. The priority of the elements in a priority queue determines the order in which elements are served (i.e., the order in which they are removed). If in any case the elements have same priority, they are served as per their ordering in the queue.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(NlogN)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# CPP Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string frequencySort(string s) {
        string res = "";
        //We will use Map For Fast Fetch
        unordered_map<char, int>m;
        for(auto c: s) m[c]++;
        auto comp = [](pair<int, char>& a, pair<int, char>& b){ return a.first < b.first; };
        //Optimized with Priority Queue
        priority_queue<pair<int, char>, vector<pair<int, char>>, decltype(comp)>pq(comp);
        for(auto x: m) pq.push({x.second, x.first});
        while(!pq.empty()){
            auto p = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            while(p.first--) res += p.second;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
